  content:
    '\n<p>The Toronto Curling Association\nwill be holding its Annual General Meeting on Tuesday, Sept. 15, 2020. The\nmeeting will be held on Zoom and will start at 7 p.m.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The meeting is open to curling\nfacility managers, club member representatives, our committee members, special\nguests and curlers from our TCA member clubs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Registration is required in\nadvance and may be completed by emailing to TCA Secretary Jackie Deschenes\nat <a href="mailto:jackied@oshawagolf.com">jackied@oshawagolf.com</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We look forward to seeing you\nthere!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>AGM Agenda</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>1.              Call\nto Order</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2.              Report\non Credentials </p>\n\n\n\n<p>3.              Approval\nof Agenda </p>\n\n\n\n<p>4.              Approval\nof 2019 AGM Minutes</p>\n\n\n\n<p>5.              Acknowledgements/Updates</p>\n\n\n\n<p>6.              Financial\nStatements</p>\n\n\n\n<p>7.              Championships\nUpdate </p>\n\n\n\n<p>8.              WECC\nUpdate </p>\n\n\n\n<p>9.              Communications\nUpdate </p>\n\n\n\n<p>10.           CurlON\nUpdate </p>\n\n\n\n<p>11.           Outstanding\nContribution Award Presentation</p>\n\n\n\n<p>12.           Election </p>\n\n\n\n<p>13.           Q&A\nSession </p>\n\n\n\n<p>14.           Adjourn\nMeeting </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Call for volunteers to join the\nTCA Board and Committees</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>As part of our engagement effort,\nthe TCA is looking for individuals who are passionate about curling to join our\nteam of volunteers who serve on our Board and committees. Bring your skills and\nplanning expertise to a team that is driven to achieve results. If you are\ninterested in putting forth a nomination, please email TCA Secretary Jackie\nDeschenes at <a href="mailto:jackied@oshawagolf.com">jackied@oshawagolf.com</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Outstanding Contribution Award</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Does anyone at your club\ndeserve some recognition? Now’s the time to nominate them. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once each year, we stop to\nrecognize the many contributions made by those individuals who keep the curling\nclocks ticking.   </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The TCA’s annual Outstanding\nContribution Award is awarded to a member of a GTA club for anything from their\non-ice accomplishments to their efforts organizing open-competitive club\nleagues—and everything in between.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t let this season’s good deeds go unnoticed — nominate someone now: <a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/TCA">https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/TCA</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Deadline for 2020 submissions is September 1, 2020</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Danielle Inglis</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>President, Toronto Curling Association</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>647-523-1264</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>For more information on the TCA’s response to COVID-19,\nplease visit our website at <a href="http://www.torontocurling.com/COVID-19/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">www.torontocurling.com/COVID-19/</a></em></p>\n',
